==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*fangan'', from an Indo-European root ''*pang-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[fa|fā]], Old Saxon [[fahan]], Old High German [[fahan]], Old Norse ''fá'', Gothic [[𐍆𐌰𐌷𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[pangere]] ‘fix’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /fo:n/

===Verb===
'''fōn''' (class VII strong: '''fēhþ''' ‘he seizes’, '''fēng''' ‘he seized’, '''fēngon''' ‘they seized’, ('''ġe''')'''fangen''' past participle)
# to [[seize]]

